$timescale 1ns $end
$comment
  Non-ISO (original Bosch) CAN-FD frames. The 4-bit stuff-count + parity field
  is OMITTED — the CRC immediately follows the data field. Decode with
  fd_iso=false. Two frames:
  FD1: 29-bit ID=0x1234567, DLC=8 (8 bytes), BRS=true, ESI=false, CRC-17.
  FD2: 29-bit ID=0x0ABCDEF, DLC=9 (12 bytes), BRS=false, ESI=false, CRC-17.
  Bit period: 2000 ns (500 kbit/s at 1ns timescale). nominal_bit_period=2000.
  Regenerate via: dart run tool/generate_can_fixtures.dart
$end
$scope module tb $end
  $var wire 1 ! can_rx $end
$upscope $end
$enddefinitions $end
$dumpvars
1!
$end
